Parliament, Monday, 07 May 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Basic Education will tomorrow receive a progress report on the implementation of the Three-Stream Model and plans for the fourth industrial revolution, which among other things entails including entrepreneurship into the curriculum. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Tuesday, 08 May 2018
	Time: 9:30 am
	Venue: Committee Room V227, Second Floor, Old Assembly Chamber ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION, MS NOMALUNGELO GINA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za The Bill of Rights guarantees the right to assemble, demonstrate, picket and present petitions as long as this is done in a peaceful way and the protesters are unarmed.Read more